<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,582,966]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
The following four species are part of the 
<taxonomicName box="[672,874,582,606]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarmorata">
<emphasis box="[672,874,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. submarmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, herein designated owing to the similarity of the marbled forewings pattern, the coremata shape (two fusiform sacks, in contrast with the oval ones in other 
<taxonomicName box="[249,349,654,678]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[249,349,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species), and male genitalia (e.g., similar shape of distal end of the valva; vesica lacking tiny thorns in the lobe with the cornutus). The group consists of eight species, seven of which are divided into two subgroups according to the female genitalia: 
<number box="[663,675,726,750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" value="1.0">1</number>
) 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante, 2009" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[695,990,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discreta">
<emphasis box="[695,816,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. discreta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Durante" box="[825,990,726,750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" refString="Durante, A. (2009) Revision of the Afrotropical species of Asura Walker, 1854 (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae, Lithosiinae), with the description of a new genus. Zootaxa, 2280, 27 - 52." type="journal article" year="2009">
Durante, 
<number box="[931,990,726,750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1002,1109,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duplex" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1002,1109,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. duplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1118,1183,727,751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1118,1183,727,751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1197,1323,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aetheria" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1197,1323,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. aetheria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1332,1397,727,751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1332,1397,727,751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<number box="[260,275,762,786]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" value="2.0">2</number>
) 
<taxonomicName box="[292,449,763,787]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis box="[292,449,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[463,579,763,787]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camilla" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[463,579,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. camilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[586,650,763,787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[586,650,763,787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kiriakoff, 1958" authorityName="Kiriakoff" authorityYear="1958" box="[664,1064,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarmorata">
<emphasis box="[664,861,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. submarmorata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kiriakoff" box="[875,1055,762,786]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" refString="Kiriakoff, S. G. (1958) Ruwenzori Expedition 1952, Arctiidae (except Nolinae) Thyretidae and Notodontidae. London (British Museum (Natural History )), 1 (2 / 3), 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1958">
Kiriakoff, 
<number box="[995,1055,762,786]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" value="1958.0">1958</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The female of 
<taxonomicName box="[1240,1339,763,787]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fracta" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1240,1339,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">A. fracta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1410,763,787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1410,763,787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unknown, so at the moment it is not included in these subgroups and in the subsequent keys. The character of the female genitalia upon which the two subgroups are proposed works well as a synapomorphy of each subgroup: in the first subgroup the ductus seminalis arises directly from the corpus bursae or from what could be considered a very small appendix; in the second subgroup the ductus seminalis arises from a conspicuous cervix rotating ca. 
<number box="[151,198,942,966]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" value="270.0">270</number>
Â°.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1051,1050,1075]" box="[151,1051,1050,1075]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,739,1050,1075]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
Keys to the 
<taxonomicName box="[292,572,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarmorata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[292,572,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Afrasura submarmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
(based on female genitalia)
</paragraph>
